UK-BORN Nigerian DJ Sogood has concluded plans to stamp his feet on the sands of time with further involvement in Afrobeats. After working with Tiwa Savage, Wizkid, and Davido at different times, the disc jockey, who combines being a media personality, event host, promoter, and entrepreneur, said he is set to take a spot on the Nigerian music scene while conquering the world. “I am coming to make my mark in the industry. My accomplishments are evident for all to see. I dropped a new song weeks ago and there are more to come. Music lovers should be ready. I am set to make them feel so good,” he said.   Make Music Lagos returns for 2022 Edition     Alliance Française, Trace TV to celebrate World Music Day     Not everyone is a fan of mainstream music, Hembadoon   The well-traveled showbiz personality has collaborated with global stars that include Dream, and Weeknd. For one who started his journey into the world of music selling music CDs out of his dad’s shop in Peckham, London, DJ Sogood has traveled around the world and continues to collaborate with foreign and local music acts. Heavily influenced by Afrobeats, soca and dancehall, DJ Sogood made a mark for himself on the social and entertainment scene in the UK by co-founding Afromodelawards. With Afro Model Awards, DJ Sogood and his partners have continued to recognise, acknowledge and reward models, photographers, agencies, personalities, makeup artist, designers, and innovators throughout the fashion and style industry while creating a global platform for fashion and style models.